  "summary": "Malicious code in @bobfrankston/mlproc (npm)",
  "details": "This package is a mail processing tool that reads emails from a queue directory, parses them, and routes them to recipients via SMTP or IMAP delivery. No lifecycle hooks execute on install. No obfuscation, no network exfiltration endpoints, and no credential theft mechanisms were found in the code. The package has a public GitHub repository and has been published across 10 versions over several months. No malicious behaviour was observed in this version.",
